titleStmt.title: Papers concerning the treaty of the commissioners at Marston, met to treat for the surrender of Oxford to Sir Thomas Fairfax for the use of the Parliament. With the perfect copie of the articles, argued between the commissioners on both sides, for the surrender of Bostoll Garrison, on Wednesday, Iune the 10. 1646. With all the ordnance. armes and ammunition bag and baggage. These are true copies of the originall papers, and printed and published according to order of Parliament.
titleStmt.author: N. T.
England and Wales. Parliament.

notesStmt.note: Consists of two documents, the first of which is a letter dated and signed: Marston the 7. of Iune, 1646. N.T.
Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
